tldr: The sleep questionnaire app received a comprehensive aesthetic overhaul,
  transitioning from a generic look to a calming, professional, and sleep-themed
  design. This involved updating the color palette, redesigning the main form
  layout, enhancing UI components, and applying consistent styling across all
  sections, along with a minor bug fix for input values.
overview: "The user initiated a comprehensive aesthetic review for their sleep
  questionnaire app, aiming to elevate its visual appeal from a generic template
  to a more calming and professional sleep-themed experience. The approach
  involved a multi-faceted redesign: a new color palette with deep indigos,
  purples, and teal accents was introduced, along with custom CSS utilities. The
  main form layout was enhanced with subtle background blurs and a redesigned
  progress indicator. The welcome screen was transformed with a hero section and
  interactive feature cards. All core UI components like checkboxes, radio
  buttons, sliders, and cards received significant styling improvements,
  including better hover states and visual feedback. Crucially, the agent
  systematically updated all 14 questionnaire sections to ensure consistent
  application of the new theme, replacing old gray-boxed groupings with refined
  card-style elements. The report section was also polished with consistent card
  headers and improved content presentation. Additionally, a minor bug related
  to  values in input fields was identified and fixed, ensuring a smoother
  user experience. The outcome is a visually cohesive, professional, and
  aesthetically pleasing application that aligns with the calming nature of a
  sleep health assessment."
